<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4712.3.3>
    bibo:endPage "376" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2019-12-20" ;
    bibo:startPage "365" ;
    bibo:volume "4712" ;
    dc:creator "Morffe, Jans; García, Nayla; Hasegawa, Koichi; Carreno, Ramon A." ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Aoruroides Travassos & Kloss, 1958 (Nematoda: Oxyuridomorpha Thelastomatidae) parasite of the wood-burrowing cockroach Panesthia angustipennis spadica (Shiraki, 1906) (Blattodea: Blaberidae: Panesthiinae) from Japan with comments on the validity of the genus Aoruroides" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586352>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586354>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586356>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586358> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586352>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Aoruroides chubudaigaku n. sp. (Nematoda: Oxyuridomorpha: Thelastomatidae). Female.A. Oesophageal region, lateral view. B. Tail, lateral view. C. Cephalic end, en face view (reconstructed from SEM images). D. Cephalic end (reconstruct- ed from SEM images). E. Vagina vera and vagina uterina, lateral view. F. Genital tract, lateral view. G. Habitus, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3586352/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586354>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Aoruroides chubudaigaku n. sp. (Nematoda: Oxyuridomorpha: Thelastomatidae). Male. A. Oesophageal region, lateral view. B. Tail, lateral view. C. Cephalic end, en face view (reconstructed from SEM images). D. Cloacal region, ventral view (reconstructed from SEM images). E. Distal end of the post-cloacal appendage, ventral view (reconstructed from SEM images). F. Habitus, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3586354/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586356>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Aoruroides chubudaigaku n. sp. (Nematoda: Oxyuridomorpha: Thelastomatidae). SEM images. Female. A. Cephalic end. B. Cephalic end, en face view. C. Vulva, ventral view. D. Anus, ventro-lateral view. Male. E. Cephalic end. F. Cephalic end, en face view. G. Cloacal region, ventro-lateral view. H. Cloacal region, ventral view (detail of the distal end of the post-cloacal appendage at the inferior left corner of the picture). Scale bars: A, C, D. 20 µm. B, G, H. 10 µm. E, F. 5 µm. Detail of the post-cloacal appendage. 2 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3586356/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586358>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Maximum likelihood (ML) tree inferred from the D2-D3 LSU rDNA for several species of the family Thelastomatidae (Nematoda: Oxyuridomorpha: Thelastomatoidea). Hystrignathus sp. (Hystrignathidae), Cameronia multiovata (Thelastomatidae) and three species of Travassosinema (Travassosinematidae) were used as outgroup taxa (in red). Values at the nodes correspond to bootstrap resampling (≥70)/posterior probability (≥0.90). Newly obtained sequences in bold." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3586358/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

